thread.title: Interstate 5 reopens after overnight crash, southbound closure
thread.title_full: Interstate 5 reopens after overnight crash, southbound closure | OregonLive.com

author: Stuart Tomlinson | The Oregonian/OregonLive
title: Interstate 5 reopens after overnight crash, southbound closure
text:
Interstate 5 has reopened to southbound traffic through the Rose Quarter area of Portland.
Workers spent nearly six hours cleaning up from a 1 a.m. truck accident near the Rose Quarter , at exit 301. A southbound truck became stuck on the center wall between northbound and southbound lanes, according to early reports.
Drivers heading south on I-5 were redirected onto Interstate 405 during the road closure. Northbound I-5 was closed for a short period of time; it reopened before the morning rush hour started.
